The paper deals with the concept of sparsity in signals and dictionaries, which is a common topic in information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The paper also discusses the legitimacy of atoms in a sparse representation, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the paper introduces an uncertainty principle for random sparse signals, which is a topic in both information theory and signal processing, as well as in statistics (cs.SI).
